column7: Title:	Commemoration 22.03 - operational impact  Body:	On 22.03.2017 there will be a commemoration ceremony at Brussels Airport. This will have following operational impact: From 0645 to 0710 utc no departures will be allowed. RWY 25L will be in use for all arrivals with an arrival rate of 32 aircraft per hour. RWY 25R will be available for emergency traffic only. From 0658 to 0659 all traffic will be requested to hold position to participate in 1 minute of silence. NOTAMS A0597/17 and A0598/17 refer. We thank you for your understanding.

column8: THREE ALTERNATIVE TIME WINDOWS HAVE BEEN PLANNED. OPERATIONAL SIMULATIONS HAVE SHOWN THAT THE DEPARTURE CAPACITY OF FRANKFURT MAIN AIRPORT WILL BE LIMITED TO A MAXIMUM OF 42 TAKE-OFFS PER HOUR DURING THE TIME OF THE COMPLETE CLOSURE.  ALL AIRLINES USING FRANKFURT MAIN AIRPORT ARE URGENTLY REQUESTED TO CHECK WHETHER IT IS POSSIBLE TO CANCEL CERTAIN FLIGHTS (ARRIVAL AND DEPARTURE) DURING THE TIME OF THE COMPLETE CLOSURE ON 25 AND 26 MAY 2017 AS WELL AS ON 27 MAY 2017
column9: WHICH IS THE SECOND DAY OF THE FIRST ALTERNATIVE WINDOW. ANY CANCELLATIONS IN CONNECTION WITH THIS MEASURE WILL NOT HAVE A NEGATIVE IMPACT ON THE 'GRANDFATHER RULE' FOR SUBSEQUENT SCHEDULING PERIODS. IF IT BECOMES OBVIOUS THAT THE DEMAND FOR DEPARTURES IN THE OPERATIONAL HOURS DURING THE FULL CLOSURE WILL EXCEED 42 TAKE-OFFS PER HOUR
column10: AIR TRAFFIC FLOW MANAGEMENT MEASURES WILL BE IMPLEMENTED. THE EXISTING NIGHT CURFEWS WILL REMAIN UNCHANGED DURING THE TIME  OF THE CONSTRUCTION MEASURE. /Tommi

From 19th May 04:00UTC until 20th May 04:00UTC   So far neither the union nor the DSNA have published any official announcements (NOTAM etc.) However, it is expected that various telcos will be hosted on Tuesday the 17th May.  We expect that the strike will impact flights operating to:-  •	Spain (incl. Canaries) •	Portugal  •	Morocco  •	France  And that the French authorities could mandate that AOs cancel flights to/from ORY, CDG and/or NCE.  Therefore please review your contingency measures and be prepared to implement these at  short notice.

A French national call to strike  is planned next Thursday, May 19th 2016.  Several public service unions have echoed this call, including USAC-CGT for the DGAC .  We expect that the strike will impact flights operating to:-  •	Spain (incl. Canaries) •	Portugal  •	Morocco  •	France  And that the French authorities could mandate that AOs cancel flights to/from ORY, CDG and/or NCE.  Therefore please review your contingency measures and be prepared to implement these at  short notice.

column10: they expect the following:   EN-ROUTE  Reims ACC (LFEE): Pre-Tactical regulations should be lifted early in the morning (before 0600utc) and other regulations will be put in the afternoon (1300-1745utc) to ensure the shift handover.  Marseilles ACC (LFMM): they expect to be above the minimum service rather early in the morning.  Paris ACC (LFFF): West cluster should not be too much affected
column11: they hope to cancel all regulations early in the morning.  Paris ACC (LFFF): East cluster should remain on minimum service all day long.  Brest ACC (LFRR): a bit similar to Reims
column12: all regulations cancelled early in the morning and other will be implemented in the afternoon (till 1800utc) to ensure the shift handover.  Bordeaux ACC (LFBB): they do not expect to cancel the Pre-Tactical regulations before 0600utc. Possibility of others in the afternoon..   AIRPORTS  LFPO: there will be regulations in the morning and maybe some in the afternoon also. It is requested to airlines to reduce their flight program by 15%.  LFPG: we might have regulation in place but they do not expect important delay during the day.  LFML: they do not expect difficult situation during the day.  LFBD: regulations will be running all day generating a difficult situation.     (occ/mg)

Info published by TI on 26.1 / more info see flagged Email to 26.1:  We have been receiving indications of a possible strike by Hungarian ATC next week Tuesday (Jan. 31) for the full day. This action could also affect Kosovo (KFOR) overflights since this airspace is controlled by the Hungarian ANSP. No NOTAM has been issued so far
column8: and it is unclear what the capacity reduction(s) would be for both airspace and airports. There should be no zero-rate restrictions
column9: but a significant delay impact for flights in/out/thru Hungarian controlled airspace would be anticipated.  Negotiations are ongoing
column10: and a decision is expected on Saturday.

column7: Update on French strike.  I do confirm that:  ·         the only National strike day officially called is for 21st Sept 0000-2359 lt – NO strike called for 22nd and 23rd Sept ·         the National strike was called by CGT

column7: You may be aware that tomorrow, 19th October, another public service strike is taking place in France.   Whilst the strike has not been relayed by the ATC unions, and no NOTAMs have been issued, there remains a small risk of disruption by way of isolated participation.   DSNA are keen to keep the strike low profile, and in light of no NOTAMs, no NOP Headline News has been issued.    Based on information received so far, we expect the following: •	Strike regulations for Marseille East starting this evening from 1800z onwards. The expectation is that these regulations should be cancelled shortly prior to the start time. •	Some regulations for Marseille East can be expected for the early morning which we also anticipate will be cancelled. •	No participation is foreseen by the other French ACC’s / airports •	No mitigation measures are currently being taken by NMOC, however we remain prepared for any additional degradation of service.

column7: Hei,  OSL released the attached today (English information was requested at AOC meeting also)  There is the possibility of Security Unions not reaching an agreement this week during negotiations, worst case scenario is airport terminal closure to public Friday 10th June from 06:00 (Local Time).   OSL currently aren’t sure if this will affect inbound passengers and transfers.  If your flight(s) were to be cancelled, crews can still use the airport, aircraft would likely be able to position out empty.  --  In addition, SAS Pilots might strike this coming Thursday 9th June, this would likely immediately fill all our handled flights to capacity. SGH are currently planning extra rebooking facilities in the terminal.  Brgds,  Ben King Key Account Manager | Menzies Aviation OSL  Update friday 0305z: No strike at Oslo Airport  As there will be no strike, we will remain open as usual, but there could be some minor delays as a consequence of the uncertain situation we have had leading up to the potential strike," says head of communications Joachim Westher Andersen at Oslo Airport...Staffing in the security check will immediately be maintained at the planned level in order to handle the traffic volume expected over the course of the day on Friday"

column7: BRUSSELS 29.09  As stated before
column8: we do expect an impact on our staffing as a result of the national manifestation that will take place tomorrow. We would like to re-iterate that this manifestation does not target  Swissport or any of it subsidiaries
column9: and is instead aimed at our current government’s socio-economical policy.  To minimalize the consequences
column10: we have planned additional staff and volunteers to support our operations.  We remain committed to our mission of a continuous and qualitative service
column11: and are doing everything within our power to provide you with a satisfactory service.  Our Loading department will be affected the most. According to current estimations
column12: we will be working with about 70% of our planned personnel within this division.  The impact on other departments (Cleaning
column13: Baggage Control
column14: Load control
column15: Passenger Services) should be small to non-existent.    In order to streamline our joint operations in BRU tomorrow
column16: we kindly ask you to limit cargo as much as possible.  This will allow our loading teams and their support to focus on loading and offloading bags. Furthermore
column17: any cleaning performed in outstations would provide a welcome relief for our cleaning teams

We regret to inform you that a strike has been called by Trablisa (private security company) unions in Palma airport (PMI). The labor action has been called for Tuesdays and Saturdays starting on July the 11th till July the 29th from 04:00 to 08:00
column8: from 12:00 to 14:00 and from 18:00 to 23:59 local time. Minimum services settled by the government have been to cover the 100%. Although it is not expected any severe security services disruption we suggest you to advice your passengers to bring forward the arrival time to the airport in the case the security filter services are congested. Anyway Iberia will do its utmost to minimize any impact to your operation. We will keep you informed of any new regarding this action.

column7: Spain - Airport Security Strike - Barcelona Began 28 Jul 2017 Expires on 09 Aug 2017 .. Airport security to strike at Barcelona, Spain, airport (BCN) from Aug. 4. Expect long waits at security lines, possible flight disruptions.  Summary Unionized security guards at Barcelona-El Prat (BCN) International Airport announced plans to strike starting Aug. 4.   The strike will only take place during specific periods: 0530-0630, 1030-1130, 1630-1730, and 1830-1930 every Friday, Sunday, and Monday. However, the guards have begun a work-to-rule" action that has already resulted in significant delays at security checkpoints. Delays have been most severe in Terminal 1, at times reaching two hours"

column7: Dear All   Following received from AAHK re-direct for your info.   Quote Listed below are major points to note for the 2nd Weather Briefing held at 1200 hrs today:   1.  HKO •       Khanun is forcast to move Northwest at 8 knots and will likely intensify into Typhoon on Sunday.  It will be closest to CLK at around 300 km to Southwest around 1700 hrs Sunday afternoon. •       Strong Easterly wind across Lantau Island mainly from the East may bring some low level windsherar and turbulence Sunday morning till Monday morning.  There is chance of cross wind larger than 25 knots.   •       TC Signal No. 3 may be considered later today and higher TC Signal on Sunday cannot be ruled out. •       Heavy shower occasionally from Sunday afternoon.   2.  ATC •       Foresee normal operations for Saturday.  Some go-around and mis-approach are possible Sunday.   •       Dual runway operations Sunday night over Monday morning.   3.  Airfield/AA •       Based on the weather forecast
column8: FRCS is not planned on Sunday.  However
column9: if weather condition changes drastically on Sunday
column10: FRCS may be considered for Monday.    4.  ADM/AA •       APM service will be extended on Sunday over Monday morning  and will coordinate with public transport operators to strengthen the transport service if needed.  Airport community will be updated accordingly.    5.  Airlines •       CX and HX advised normal operations planned for their flights. column7: HKG:  Dear All   Following received from AAHK re-direct for your info.   Quote Listed below are major points to note for the 2nd Weather Briefing held at 1200 hrs today:   1.  HKO •       Khanun is forcast to move Northwest at 8 knots and will likely intensify into Typhoon on Sunday.  It will be closest to CLK at around 300 km to Southwest around 1700 hrs Sunday afternoon. •       Strong Easterly wind across Lantau Island mainly from the East may bring some low level windsherar and turbulence Sunday morning till Monday morning.  There is chance of cross wind larger than 25 knots.   •       TC Signal No. 3 may be considered later today and higher TC Signal on Sunday cannot be ruled out. •       Heavy shower occasionally from Sunday afternoon.   2.  ATC •       Foresee normal operations for Saturday.  Some go-around and mis-approach are possible Sunday.   •       Dual runway operations Sunday night over Monday morning.   3.  Airfield/AA •       Based on the weather forecast

column7: Brussels reopened for limited number of flights.   1. BRU situation and restricted capacity valid for the 2 – 8 May 2016  - Pax throughput in the heavily damaged terminal is the limiting factor
column8: resulting in 28 departures an hour - Curb site (in front of the terminal) is not available for cars (meet and greet has been abandoned).  (this is likely to continue) - 100 % security checks are performed by the policy well before the Terminal building and cars can only go to the car park areas (The airport wants to change this situation)  - Pax to Africa are offered to bring their luggage to a facility outside the Airport (i.e. BRU Cargo) one day before their flight to avoid capacity issues in the Terminal - Pax have to show a valid travel document to be allowed to enter the Terminal Building  2. column7: People  from terminal at JFK evacuated after unconfirmed reports of shots fired.  Police are evacuating Terminal 8 at JFK airport in New York after Port Authority Police received a call of shots  fired in the departures area, according to spokesman Joe Pentangelo. There are currently no injuries, no arrests and no confirmation of shots fired. However, Port Authority police are evacuating the terminal at this time to be cautious, Pentangelo said. A ground stop has been issued at the airport due to security" until 11:30 p.m. ET, according to the FAA command system website."

column7: With effective from the end of Jul2017, HKG CAD and Hong Kong Airport Authority will implement a project of A-CDM ( Airport-Collaborate Decision Making) at Hong Kong International Airport. It is a joint initiative between all airport partners, airport Authority, Air Traffic Control (CAD), Airline Operators(AO) and the ground handlers(GH). The objective is for airport partners to work together to facilitate the sharing of timely and accurate operational data which can optimize the turnaround process and assure the best possible co-ordination of resources.  7.	Proposed Phased implementation From 31Jul2017(planning), Phase 1 of inputting TOBT for flights with EOBT 0200-0600LT (approximately 2 weeks) From 15Aug2017(estimate), Phase 2 of inputting TOBT for flights with EOBT 0001-0600LT (approximately 1 month) From 15Sep2017(estimate), Phase 3 of inputting TOBT for flights with EOBT 0001-1200LT (approximately 2 months) From 15Nov2017(estimate), Phase 4 of inputting TOBT for all HKG departure flight.  ____  Starting from on July 14th to August 17th , the Vilnius Airport will be closed for the reconstruction of the runway.
